[[File:WasedaDori2004-12-11.jpg|thumb|240px|right|Intersection in Nishi-Waseda (December 2004)]]
'''Waseda Street''' (わせだどおり) is the common name (東京都通称道路名) for a section of road running from {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京|12=draft}}{{ill|Chiyoda City|ja|千代町区|12=draft}} to {{ill|Suginami City|ja|杉並区|12=draft}}. It is composed of parts of {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 25|ja|東京都道・埼玉県道25号飯田橋石神井新座線|12=draft}} and the entirety of {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 438|ja|東京都道438号向井町新町線|12=draft}}<ref name="token">{{Cite web|lang=ja|url=http://www.kensetsu.metro.tokyo.jp/content/000006219.pdf|title=パンフ用全図_pdf|accessdate=2017-11-12|format=PDF|publisher=Tokyo Metropolitan Construction Bureau}}</ref>. It was formerly called '''Showa Street''' (昭和通り)<ref>{{Cite book|lang=ja|title=Nakano City History, Showa Edition 3|publisher=Tokyo {{ill|Nakano City|ja|中野区|12=draft}}|year=1973|page=697}} ([https://dl.ndl.go.jp/ja/pid/9641100/1/365 Online version], National Diet Library Digital Collection) where it states "''Showa Street (currently Waseda Street)''".</ref>.

This article also describes the '''Old Waseda Street''' (旧わせだどおり), which branches from Waseda Street in {{ill|Suginami City|ja|杉並区|12=draft}} and leads to {{ill|Nerima City|ja|純馬区|12=draft}}.

== Overview ==
Waseda Street runs from the Tayasumon Intersection (Yasukuni Street) in Kudankita, Chiyoda City, passing through {{ill|Nishi-Waseda|ja|西日田|12=draft}}, {{ill|Nakano City|ja|中野区|12=draft}} Nakano, and ends at Kamigusa, Suginami City (on Ome Highway). It initially heads northwest from Yasukuni Street, gradually shifts to west-northwest, and finally southwest to connect with Ome Highway at its terminus. Old Waseda Street diverges from Waseda Street at the Hontanumacho 2-chome intersection in Suginami City and heads northwest, terminating in Shakujidai, Nerima City. Both names were assigned by the Tokyo Metropolitan Construction Bureau<ref name="ichiran">{{Cite web|lang=ja|url=http://www.kensetsu.metro.tokyo.jp/content/000006190.pdf|title=Route List|accessdate=2017-11-12|format=PDF|publisher=Tokyo Metropolitan Construction Bureau}}</ref>. Additionally, the section of Waseda Street between the Kagurazaka-shita and Kagurazaka-ue intersections (within Shinjuku City) is also known as "{{ill|Kagurazaka Street|ja|神楽坂通り|12=draft}}" as designated by Shinjuku City<ref>{{Cite web|lang=ja|url=http://www.city.shinjuku.lg.jp/content/000106777.pdf|title=000106777.pdf (Road Alias Map)|accessdate=2017-11-12|format=PDF|publisher=Shinjuku City}}</ref>.

In Shinjuku City, the Kagurazaka Street section is a reversible one-way road: eastbound in the morning and westbound in the afternoon. Additionally, near the terminus of Old Waseda Street, traffic flows one-way toward its starting point.

The name "Waseda Street" was originally designated for the section from "Tayasumon{{~}}{{ill|Hoya New Road Intersection|ja|保谷新道交差点|12=draft}}." However, in 1984, the designation was revised to cover "Tayasumon to {{ill|Igusa Hachiman Shrine|ja|井草八幡宮|lt=Igusa Hachiman|12=draft}}." Consequently, the section from Hontanumacho 2-chome to the Hoya New Road Intersection, excluded from the revised Waseda Street designation, was assigned the name "Old Waseda Street." As of 2017, the "Old Waseda Street" designation applies only to the section up to the Fuji Highway intersection; the remaining section from the Fuji Highway intersection to the Hoya New Road Intersection lacks a designation.

== Starting and Ending Points ==
; Waseda Street
* Starting Point: {{ill|Tayasumon Intersection|ja|田安門交差点|12=draft}} (千代町区九段北 2<ref name="ichiran" />) - {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 302|ja|東京都道302号新宿両国線|12=draft}} (Yasukuni Street) Intersection<ref group="note">Located within an overlapping section with {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 401|ja|東京都道401号麻岐町竹平線|12=draft}} (Uchibori Street)</ref>
* Ending Point: {{ill|Igusa Hachimanmae Intersection|ja|井草八幡前交差点|12=draft}} (杉並区上井草 4<ref name="ichiran" />) - {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 4|ja|東京都道・埼玉県道4号東京所沢線|12=draft}} (Ome Highway) Intersection

; Old Waseda Street
* Starting Point: {{ill|Hontanumacho 2-chome Intersection|ja|本天江町 2 丁目 交差点|12=draft}} (杉並区 下井草1<ref name="ichiran" />) - Intersection with {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 25|ja|東京都道・埼玉県道25号飯田橋石神井新座線|12=draft}} / {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 438|ja|東京都道438号向井町新町線|12=draft}}
* Ending Point: {{ill|Unnamed Intersection|ja|(名称なし交差点)|12=draft}} (純馬区 石神井台 5<ref name="ichiran" />) - Intersection with {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 8|ja|東京都道8号千代町純馬田無線|12=draft}} (Fuji Highway)


