[[File:WasedaDori2004-12-11.jpg|thumb|240px|right|Intersection in Nishi-Waseda (December 2004)]]
'''Waseda Street''' (わせだどおり) is the common name (東京都通称道路名) for a section of road running from {{ill|Tokyo|ja|東京|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo|qq=}}{{ill|Chiyoda City|ja|千代町区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiyoda City|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} to [[:en:Suginami|Suginami City]]. It is composed of parts of {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 25|ja|東京都道・埼玉県道25号飯田橋石神井新座線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo Metropolitan Route 25|qq=}} and the entirety of {{ill|Tokyo Metropolitan Route 438|ja|東京都道438号向井町新町線|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo Metropolitan Route 438|qq=}}<ref name="token">{{Cite web|lang=ja|url=http://www.kensetsu.metro.tokyo.jp/content/000006219.pdf|title=パンフ用全図_pdf|accessdate=2017-11-12|format=PDF|publisher=Tokyo Metropolitan Construction Bureau}}</ref>. It was formerly called '''Showa Street''' (昭和通り)<ref>{{Cite book|lang=ja|title=Nakano City History, Showa Edition 3|publisher=Tokyo [[:en:Nakano, Tokyo|Nakano City]]|year=1973|page=697}} ([https://dl.ndl.go.jp/ja/pid/9641100/1/365 Online version], National Diet Library Digital Collection) where it states "''Showa Street (currently Waseda Street)''".</ref>.

This article also describes the '''Old Waseda Street''' (旧わせだどおり), which branches from Waseda Street in [[:en:Suginami|Suginami City]] and leads to {{ill|Nerima City|ja|純馬区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nerima City|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

== Overview ==
Waseda Street runs from the Tayasumon Intersection (Yasukuni Street) in Kudankita, Chiyoda City, passing through {{ill|Nishi-Waseda|ja|西日田|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nishi-Waseda|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, [[:en:Nakano, Tokyo|Nakano City]] Nakano, and ends at Kamigusa, Suginami City (on Ome Highway). It initially heads northwest from Yasukuni Street, gradually shifts to west-northwest, and finally southwest to connect with Ome Highway at its terminus. Old Waseda Street diverges from Waseda Street at the Hontanumacho 2-chome intersection in Suginami City and heads northwest, terminating in Shakujidai, Nerima City. Both names were assigned by the Tokyo Metropolitan Construction Bureau<ref name="ichiran">{{Cite web|lang=ja|url=http://www.kensetsu.metro.tokyo.jp/content/000006190.pdf|title=Route List|accessdate=2017-11-12|format=PDF|publisher=Tokyo Metropolitan Construction Bureau}}</ref>. Additionally, the section of Waseda Street between the Kagurazaka-shita and Kagurazaka-ue intersections (within Shinjuku City) is also known as "{{ill|Kagurazaka Street|ja|神楽坂通り|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kagurazaka Street|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 早稲田通り}}" as designated by Shinjuku City<ref>{{Cite web|lang=ja|url=http://www.city.shinjuku.lg.jp/content/000106777.pdf|title=000106777.pdf (Road Alias Map)|accessdate=2017-11-12|format=PDF|publisher=Shinjuku City}}</ref>.

In Shinjuku City, the Kagurazaka Street section is a reversible one-way road: eastbound in the morning and westbound in the afternoon. Additionally, near the terminus of Old Waseda Street, traffic flows one-way toward its starting point.

The name "Waseda Street" was originally designated for the section from "Tayasumon{{~}}{{ill|Hoya New Road Intersection|ja|保谷新道交差点|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hoya New Road Intersection|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}." However, in 1984, the designation was revised to cover "Tayasumon to {{ill|Igusa Hachiman Shrine|ja|井草八幡宮|lt=Igusa Hachiman|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Igusa Hachiman Shrine|qq=}}." Consequently, the section from Hontanumacho 2-chome to the Hoya New Road Intersection, excluded from the revised Waseda Street designation, was assigned the name "Old Waseda Street." As of 2017, the "Old Waseda Street" designation applies only to the section up to the Fuji Highway intersection; the remaining section from the Fuji Highway intersection to the Hoya New Road Intersection lacks a designation.

